## 2. FAQ
Q: Has anyone used comput3.ai to deploy GPUs? (asked by pytrex1) A: Unanswered
Q: Does the Discord plugin have functionality to allow an agent to see, monitor, and respond to support tickets? (asked by Scooter) A: There's no pre-built support-ticket-object in the Discord API but it does support bots who monitor designated channels for emoji interactions that can trigger an automated private response thread. So it should be possible. (answered by Hidden Forces)
Q: How do I contribute/add my plugin to the Eliza official repo? Do I have to create an npm package or just create a PR? (asked by Girinath) A: Unanswered

## 3. Help Interactions
Helper: Hidden Forces | Helpee: Scooter | Context: Inquiry about Discord plugin's capability to handle support tickets | Resolution: Explained that while there's no pre-built support ticket object in Discord API, bots can monitor channels for emoji reactions to trigger automated response threads
